Got you, bro. Here’s a **clean, complete list of all the routes** for your fullstack finance tracker, organized by module. This is your blueprint—you can code against it without confusion.

---

## **1. Auth Routes**

| Method | Route                   | Description                   |
| ------ | ----------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| POST   | `/auth/register`        | Register a new user           |
| POST   | `/auth/login`           | Login user, return JWT cookie |
| POST   | `/auth/logout`          | Logout user, clear cookie     |
| GET    | `/auth/me`              | Get logged-in user info       |
| POST   | `/auth/forgot-password` | Request password reset        |
| POST   | `/auth/reset-password`  | Reset password                |

---

## **2. User Routes**

| Method | Route        | Description                    |
| ------ | ------------ | ------------------------------ |
| GET    | `/users/:id` | Get user info (optional admin) |
| PATCH  | `/users/:id` | Update user info / password    |
| DELETE | `/users/:id` | Delete account (optional)      |

---

## **3. Account Routes**

| Method | Route           | Description                     |
| ------ | --------------- | ------------------------------- |
| GET    | `/accounts`     | List all user accounts          |
| GET    | `/accounts/:id` | Get single account details      |
| POST   | `/accounts`     | Create a new account            |
| PATCH  | `/accounts/:id` | Update account info (name/type) |
| DELETE | `/accounts/:id` | Delete an account               |

---

## **4. Transaction Routes**

| Method | Route               | Description                        |
| ------ | ------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| GET    | `/transactions`     | List all transactions (filterable) |
| GET    | `/transactions/:id` | Get single transaction details     |
| POST   | `/transactions`     | Add a new transaction              |
| PATCH  | `/transactions/:id` | Edit transaction                   |
| DELETE | `/transactions/:id` | Delete transaction                 |

---

## **5. Category Routes**

| Method | Route             | Description         |
| ------ | ----------------- | ------------------- |
| GET    | `/categories`     | List all categories |
| GET    | `/categories/:id` | Get single category |
| POST   | `/categories`     | Create new category |
| PATCH  | `/categories/:id` | Update category     |
| DELETE | `/categories/:id` | Delete category     |

---

## **6. Summary / Analytics Routes**

| Method | Route               | Description                        |
| ------ | ------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| GET    | `/summary`          | Total income, expense, balances    |
| GET    | `/summary/monthly`  | Monthly trends (income vs expense) |
| GET    | `/summary/category` | Expenses per category              |

---

### **Optional Advanced Routes**

* `/transactions/import` – Import CSV/JSON
* `/transactions/export` – Export CSV/JSON
* `/dashboard` – Combined endpoint for frontend dashboard (balances, trends, recent transactions)

---

